text:
We’re currently using ‘Sales Accepted Opportunities’ for the wider marketing team. But this includes all marketing activities, and the value is set manually by sales on each qualified lead.

It’s better than ‘traffic’, but still a bit loose for me.

text:
Here are the main metrics we track on our content team scorecard:
• Inbound pipeline w/ gated content as the lead source
• Sales demos w/ gated content as the lead source
• New MQLs from content gates
• New MQLs from organic search
• Organic blog traffic
• Overall blog traffic
